{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Kp7i38C6N5YgLQQ6ecDLFh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The oracle passes. Task complete.\n\n## Summary\n\nI added two new data nodes to the existing 3-node Elasticsearch cluster and relocated the `app-data` shards onto them — no operators or CRDs involved.\n\n**What I did:**\n\n1. **Created `es-new-config` ConfigMap** mirroring the live cluster's security/TLS settings (`cluster.name: es-cluster`, `discovery.seed_hosts: es-transport`, same HTTP/transport TLS certs) but adding the allocation attribute `node.attr.zone: new` and omitting `cluster.initial_master_nodes` (these nodes *join* the existing cluster rather than bootstrap one).\n\n2. **Created `es-new` StatefulSet** (2 replicas) reusing the live cluster's `es-http-tls` certs and `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret, labeled `app=elasticsearch` so they register with the `es-transport` headless service and join the cluster. The original `es` StatefulSet was left untouched at 3 replicas.\n\n3. **Relocated shards** by setting `index.routing.allocation.require.zone: new` on `app-data`, which moved its primary+replica onto `es-new-0`/`es-new-1`.\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- Cluster health: **green**, **5 nodes** ✓\n- `app-data` shards now on `es-new-0` / `es-new-1` (outside the original es-0/1/2) ✓\n- New nodes carry `zone=new`; original nodes have no zone attribute ✓\n- `es` StatefulSet still at **3/3** replicas ✓\n- Case oracle: **\"Scale-up new nodeset verified\" (exit 0)** ✓"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":520,"cache_read_input_tokens":55057,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":520},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"63262a37-d211-4304-b9dc-3420338e64ac","uuid":